net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api

Interface Builder<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the object to build.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCollectionValidatorBuilder, AbstractMapValidatorBuilder, AbstractProperty.PropertyBuilder, CharSequenceValidatorBuilder, CompareableValidatorBuilder, ComplexValidatorBuilder, NumberValidatorBuilder, ObjectValidatorBuilder, ValidatorBuilderBigDecimal, ValidatorBuilderBoolean, ValidatorBuilderCharSequence, ValidatorBuilderCollection, ValidatorBuilderCollectionOfString, ValidatorBuilderDouble, ValidatorBuilderFloat, ValidatorBuilderInstant, ValidatorBuilderInteger, ValidatorBuilderLocalDate, ValidatorBuilderLocalDateTime, ValidatorBuilderLong, ValidatorBuilderMap, ValidatorBuilderObject, ValidatorBuilderString, ValidatorBuilderTime

    public interface Builder<T>
    This is the generic interface for a builder. A builder is an object following the builder-pattern in order to build some object using a simple and fluent API.
    Since:
    7.1.0
    Author:
    hohwille

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T build()
      Creates a new instance of the object to build.

    • Method Detail

      • build

        T build()
        Creates a new instance of the object to build. If the Builder is reused, any additional changes to the Builder shall NOT have any effect on instances previously returned by this method.
        Returns:
        the object to build.
